{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida984a8b4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2489"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2489"},"text":"§ 2489.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Overseas commissary and exchange stores: access and purchase restrictions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida984a8b5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2489/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Authority to Establish Restrictions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Defense may establish restrictions on the ability of eligible patrons of commissary and exchange stores located outside of the United States to purchase certain merchandise items (or the quantity of certain merchandise items) otherwise included within an authorized merchandise category if the Secretary determines that such restrictions are necessary to prevent the resale of such merchandise in violation of treaty obligations of the United States or host nation laws (to the extent such laws are not inconsistent with United States laws).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida984a8b6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2489/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Limitations on Use of Authority","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In establishing a quantity or other restriction, the Secretary—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida984a8b7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2489/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" may not discriminate among the various categories of eligible patrons of the commissary and exchange system; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida984a8b8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2489/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" shall ensure that the restriction is consistent with the purpose of the overseas commissary and exchange system to provide reasonable access for eligible patrons to purchase merchandise items made in the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida984a8b9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/261/dA/tIII/s365/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–261, div. A, title III, § 365(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/1986"},"text":"112 Stat. 1986","children":[],"tail":", § 2492; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/65/dA/tX/s1066/a/22"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–65, div. A, title X, § 1066(a)(22)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/771"},"text":"113 Stat. 771","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314/dA/tX/s1041/a/15"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–314, div. A, title X, § 1041(a)(15)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-12-02"},"text":"Dec. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2645"},"text":"116 Stat. 2645","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 2489, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/dA/tVI/s651/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, div. A, title VI, § 651(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1971"},"text":"118 Stat. 1971","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/dA/tVI/s651"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, div. A, title VI, § 651","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1783"},"text":"126 Stat. 1783","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida984a8ba-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida984a8bb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"ida984a8bc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 2489 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2495a"},"text":"section 2495a of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 2489a was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2495b"},"text":"section 2495b of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 2490 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2868"},"text":"section 2868 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 2490a was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2488"},"text":"section 2488 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Another prior section 2490a was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2783"},"text":"section 2783 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida984a8bd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2013—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/s651/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, § 651(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (1) as subsec. (a) and added heading."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/s651/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, § 651(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), redesignated par. (2) of former subsec. (a) as (b), added heading, and redesignated subpars. (A) and (B) of former par. (2) as pars. (1) and (2), respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/s651/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, § 651(a)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (b). Text read as follows: “For each location outside the United States that is served by the commissary system or the exchange system, the Secretary of Defense may maintain a list of controlled merchandise items, except that, after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-17"},"text":"October 17, 1998","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary may not change the list to add a merchandise item unless, before making the change, the Secretary submits to Congress a notice of the proposed addition and the reasons for the addition of the item.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/s651/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, § 651(a)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (c). Text read as follows: “The Secretary of Defense shall notify Congress of any change proposed or made to any of the host nation laws or any of the treaty obligations of the United States, and any changed conditions within host nations, if the change would necessitate the use of quantity or other restrictions on purchases in commissary and exchange stores located outside the United States.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2492"},"text":"section 2492 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–314","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (c) and struck out heading and text of former subsec. (c). Text read as follows: “The Secretary of Defense shall notify Congress of any change proposed or made to any of the host nation laws or any of the treaty obligations of the United States, and any changed conditions within host nations, if the change would necessitate the use of quantity or other restrictions on purchases in commissary and exchange stores located outside the United States.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/65"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–65","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-17"},"text":"October 17, 1998","children":[],"tail":"” for “the date of the enactment of this section”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
